WEBVTT

00:08.108 --> 00:09.216
(JACINDA HUMS)

00:09.316 --> 00:11.856
(PLAYFUL MUSIC)

00:12.522 --> 00:14.171
SANTI: Mum's gonna love this.

00:14.271 --> 00:16.586
JACINDA: It's from
both of us, OK?

00:16.686 --> 00:18.045
SANTI: OK. Sure.

00:18.145 --> 00:19.377
That's a big house.

00:19.477 --> 00:20.751
-Yeah.
-And who's that?

00:20.851 --> 00:23.749
-It's you. With her.
-(SANTI LAUGHS)

00:23.849 --> 00:25.498
And me in the middle.

00:25.598 --> 00:28.263
We love you, Mum.

00:33.510 --> 00:35.177
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

00:35.842 --> 00:37.382
(DOOR OPENS)

00:43.046 --> 00:44.737
Be careful.

00:44.837 --> 00:45.611
Be
careful.

00:45.711 --> 00:48.835
-Oh, shit!
-(SHRIEKS)

00:55.246 --> 00:57.080
Happy Mother's Day?

01:01.368 --> 01:03.701
(BELL RINGS)

01:08.115 --> 01:10.030
(DOOR SQUEAKS)

01:10.905 --> 01:13.486
-Hola!
-(CHUCKLES) Hola.

01:23.522 --> 01:25.271
I'm fine!

01:36.222 --> 01:39.220
('GOOD THING' BY MAPLE GLIDER)

01:40.637 --> 01:46.217
SONG: ♪ There are no words
I have to say

01:47.216 --> 01:51.464
♪ In this moment... ♪

01:53.963 --> 01:55.753
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

01:56.919 --> 02:02.499
♪ You're asking me if I'm OK

02:03.249 --> 02:09.037
♪ But I need time
to process... ♪

02:11.953 --> 02:13.726
What are you doing?

02:13.826 --> 02:14.934
Shut up.

02:15.034 --> 02:17.990
This is my fantasy.

02:19.073 --> 02:26.152
♪ All these parts of me
I had not noticed

02:27.901 --> 02:32.066
♪ Before you came

02:37.146 --> 02:42.934
♪ I know you think
I'm being cold

02:43.350 --> 02:50.429
♪ But I can't bear
to look at you today

02:53.469 --> 02:57.701
♪ 'Cause every single time I do

02:57.801 --> 03:00.298
♪ I fear

03:00.590 --> 03:04.154
♪ It might be the last time

03:04.254 --> 03:08.710
♪ That you'll see me this way

03:10.043 --> 03:16.123
♪ Way

03:18.081 --> 03:23.660
♪ Way

03:25.492 --> 03:31.138
♪ But I guess
that's how we learn

03:31.238 --> 03:36.469
♪ By setting fire to things
that bring us life

03:36.569 --> 03:40.925
♪ Before we've got
to watch them burn

03:41.025 --> 03:47.188
♪ So I'll say goodbye... ♪

03:48.771 --> 03:51.435
Are you thinking about her?

03:53.018 --> 03:55.475
-What?
-Your mum.

03:56.307 --> 03:59.513
Mother's Day is tough
for a lot of people.

04:01.429 --> 04:03.954
Did you know that the woman
who invented Mother's Day

04:04.054 --> 04:06.660
then spent the rest of her life
trying to shut it down

04:06.760 --> 04:10.950
because it had been hijacked
by money-making arseholes?

04:11.050 --> 04:16.047
You know, Santa Claus doesn't
exist, but we still celebrate.

04:17.961 --> 04:19.027
Wait.

04:19.127 --> 04:21.667
Santa Claus doesn't exist?

04:27.289 --> 04:29.313
Seriously, though,
are you gonna see Oly today

04:29.413 --> 04:31.370
and make a fuss of her?

04:32.536 --> 04:33.435
Yeah.

04:33.535 --> 04:35.768
J and I have made her a card.

04:35.868 --> 04:38.241
Oh, that's nice.

04:40.615 --> 04:43.930
Oh, he's so cute!

04:44.030 --> 04:45.220
(WHISPERS) Vince!

04:45.320 --> 04:47.694
Wake up, Sleeping Beauty!

04:51.817 --> 04:52.925
(TALIA SIGHS)

04:53.025 --> 04:54.757
(VINCE GRUNTS) Hey.

04:54.857 --> 04:55.714
What's up?

04:55.814 --> 04:58.770
Happy Mother's Day.

05:02.893 --> 05:04.726
What then?

05:05.850 --> 05:08.098
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

05:10.888 --> 05:13.887
-I don't get it.
-(BOTH LAUGH)

05:22.424 --> 05:24.655
Is this a 12-week scan?

05:24.755 --> 05:26.738
It's OUR 12-week scan.

05:26.838 --> 05:27.487
(LAUGHS) For real?

05:27.587 --> 05:31.776
We wanted to keep it a secret
in the first trimester, but...

05:31.876 --> 05:34.774
-We're having a baby!
-(LAUGHS)

05:34.874 --> 05:38.414
Happy Mother's Day, mothers!

05:39.247 --> 05:41.079
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

05:44.577 --> 05:45.643
Oh! Hi.

05:45.743 --> 05:47.309
-Hey.
-JACINDA: Papi!

05:47.409 --> 05:50.265
(GASPS) Ah, puchita!

05:50.365 --> 05:52.864
Oh, I missed you.

05:52.990 --> 05:54.804
Have you had a special morning
with Mum?

05:54.904 --> 05:56.887
-I made toast.
-Yummy!

05:56.987 --> 05:58.967
-Put your hat on!
-OK.

05:59.067 --> 06:00.885
SANTI: That's a cool hat.

06:00.985 --> 06:02.966
JACINDA: Did you bring our card?

06:03.066 --> 06:04.549
I'm not gonna forget that.

06:04.649 --> 06:06.256
Wanna give it to her?

06:06.356 --> 06:08.354
OLY: Ohh!

06:09.437 --> 06:11.752
JACINDA: Daddy's doing
his art again.

06:11.852 --> 06:14.042
OLY: Aww! It's us!

06:14.142 --> 06:17.082
SANTI: J drew most of it.
I just helped out.

06:17.182 --> 06:20.681
Papi, you read it so I can hear.

06:21.180 --> 06:23.455
I told him what to write.

06:23.555 --> 06:25.469
She did.

06:27.218 --> 06:28.160
"Mum, I love you.

06:28.260 --> 06:32.365
"You make me pasta when
I'm hungry so I don't die."

06:32.465 --> 06:32.782
(LAUGHS)

06:32.882 --> 06:36.363
"I like when you read me books
and take me swimming.

06:36.463 --> 06:39.611
"You're not like
all the other boring mums.

06:39.711 --> 06:40.861
"You're my mum.

06:40.961 --> 06:43.568
"And that's what makes you
the best."

06:43.668 --> 06:44.442
Aww!

06:44.542 --> 06:45.400
"Love, JJ.

06:45.500 --> 06:47.690
"Kiss, hug, kiss, hug."

06:47.790 --> 06:48.815
I love you.

06:48.915 --> 06:50.855
Do you want me to keep going?

06:50.955 --> 06:52.912
Mm-hm.

06:55.202 --> 06:55.934
"Oly,

06:56.034 --> 06:58.016
"You'll always be
a superhero to me.

06:58.116 --> 07:01.823
"You're the best mum
J could hope for.

07:01.990 --> 07:04.097
"You make her life better
and mine.

07:04.197 --> 07:07.779
"I hope you know
you can always count on me.

07:09.902 --> 07:11.776
"Love, Santi."

07:12.150 --> 07:15.148
(CHUCKLES) Thank you.

07:18.855 --> 07:23.794
(DOM SHOUTS TARZAN-STYLE)
Oooooly!

07:23.894 --> 07:26.476
Hey, Baby J!

07:27.058 --> 07:29.416
I can't remember.
Who is it that I love?

07:29.516 --> 07:30.706
Dum-Dum! You love me!

07:30.806 --> 07:32.747
I do. Look who's driving.

07:32.847 --> 07:34.413
Hi, Aunty Edie!

07:34.513 --> 07:35.911
Hello, cool girl.

07:36.011 --> 07:37.494
Sorry I can't come.

07:37.594 --> 07:39.243
Mi papi's mummy's dead.

07:39.343 --> 07:41.906
-Ohh.
-She was Ita's daughter.

07:42.006 --> 07:43.074
And Ita's sad.

07:43.174 --> 07:46.030
Will you do me a favour
and look after Dita

07:46.130 --> 07:48.071
and your dad, please?

07:48.171 --> 07:48.986
Good girl.

07:49.086 --> 07:50.319
I'll see you later, OK?

07:50.419 --> 07:53.567
-Wear your hat all day, OK?
-Yes!

07:53.667 --> 07:55.316
Cool hat!

07:55.416 --> 07:55.898
Thank you.

07:55.998 --> 07:59.289
-You ready for the kidnapping?
-Yes.

07:59.539 --> 08:03.245
-Let's go!
-Say 'bye to Dum-Dum.

08:04.870 --> 08:07.409
(BELL RESOUNDS, CHIMES TINKLE)

08:15.572 --> 08:16.262
(SIGHS)

08:16.362 --> 08:20.843
Awe and adulation
to the life-giver.

08:20.943 --> 08:22.550
Oh, thank you.

08:22.650 --> 08:25.524
That was beautiful, Bowie.

08:26.356 --> 08:27.256
Ohh!

08:27.356 --> 08:28.839
-You centred?
-Mm-hm.

08:28.939 --> 08:30.421
Prepare. We have to go.

08:30.521 --> 08:32.003
(BRAKES SQUEAL SOFTLY OUTSIDE)

08:32.103 --> 08:32.795
Go?

08:32.895 --> 08:34.169
Something is happening.

08:34.269 --> 08:35.251
We don't have a lot of time.

08:35.351 --> 08:38.708
-It's Mother's Day!
-No, fuck Mother's Day.

08:38.808 --> 08:39.499
-EDITH: Angie!
-No.

08:39.599 --> 08:41.914
EDITH: Come outside!
(KNOCKS ON DOOR)

08:42.014 --> 08:42.871
We've got a surprise!

08:42.971 --> 08:44.662
Don't open that door, Bowie.

08:44.762 --> 08:46.370
Bowie, I'm SERIOUS!

08:46.470 --> 08:48.535
-Mum. Mum.
-Bowie!

08:48.635 --> 08:51.092
Mum! No, be water.

08:54.964 --> 08:57.322
I can't believe
you're in on this.

08:57.422 --> 08:59.279
Come on, Angie, we all love you!

08:59.379 --> 09:01.487
-Yeah, we do!
-Mum, get in the car.

09:01.587 --> 09:03.942
No. I'm not getting in that car.

09:04.042 --> 09:05.941
DOM: Happy Mother's Day,
darling!

09:06.041 --> 09:07.856
I don't know what
you're doing here.

09:07.956 --> 09:09.106
I'm not your mother.

09:09.206 --> 09:11.979
Well, no, I love and hate you,

09:12.079 --> 09:13.063
much like my mother.

09:13.163 --> 09:18.101
And curiously, I sometimes
accidentally phone you

09:18.201 --> 09:20.266
when I mean to dial her.

09:20.366 --> 09:22.015
That is so creepy.

09:22.115 --> 09:24.846
I thought we didn't do
Mother's Day, Oly,

09:24.946 --> 09:26.055
because Anna Jarvis had decided

09:26.155 --> 09:29.261
that it had been appropriated
by the anti-suffragist movement.

09:29.361 --> 09:31.010
Mum, I was seven
when I said that.

09:31.110 --> 09:34.008
Hmm. Didn't stop you
from using it as an excuse

09:34.108 --> 09:36.357
not to buy me any presents.

09:37.149 --> 09:39.756
-So where's my present?
-I made you milky coffee.

09:39.856 --> 09:41.129
Well, you're not my mother.

09:41.229 --> 09:43.795
Where we're going
is the present.

09:43.895 --> 09:44.669
That's deep!

09:44.769 --> 09:46.626
'Cause that works
on two levels, right?

09:46.726 --> 09:48.417
'Cause it's, like, the present,

09:48.517 --> 09:50.831
but then, like, the present.

09:50.931 --> 09:53.539
DOM: No, no.
It's not sticky tape.

09:53.639 --> 09:56.162
BOWIE: It's not here.
No, no, no.

09:56.262 --> 09:57.245
(ALL TALK AT ONCE)

09:57.345 --> 09:58.703
BOWIE: Keep going. Keep going.
Keep going.

09:58.803 --> 10:02.576
Wait, keep going. Keep going.
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

10:02.676 --> 10:03.575
Oh, my God!

10:03.675 --> 10:05.407
ALL: Surprise!

10:05.507 --> 10:06.459
OLY: Your Mother's Day
present is

10:06.469 --> 10:10.112
you get to do the thing that
you love most in this world -

10:10.212 --> 10:12.778
destroy us in competition!

10:12.878 --> 10:13.985
DOM: Yeah!

10:14.085 --> 10:15.192
I don't like that!

10:15.292 --> 10:16.483
-(KIDS LAUGH)
-Oh, come on!

10:16.583 --> 10:18.982
Oh, come on!
It's your favourite thing!

10:19.082 --> 10:20.398
Beating us to a pulp!

10:20.498 --> 10:22.397
Oh, I'm not that competitive!

10:22.497 --> 10:23.688
-OK, Mum. Remember...
-I'm not!

10:23.788 --> 10:24.658
Remember when I beat you
in Catan

10:24.668 --> 10:27.102
putting down the knight card
just as you thought you'd won?

10:27.202 --> 10:28.892
Yeah, that was cheating!
That was cheating.

10:28.992 --> 10:30.434
You're meant to show
the knight card!

10:30.534 --> 10:33.973
OK, yeah, this... This is better
than a crappy lunch.

10:34.073 --> 10:36.614
Come on, Boz. Let's go sign in.

10:38.902 --> 10:41.553
Why aren't you celebrating
your own Mother's Day?

10:41.653 --> 10:44.259
Because I wanna be
a daughter today.

10:44.359 --> 10:46.233
A good one.

10:48.980 --> 10:51.188
Happy Mother's Day.

10:51.772 --> 10:53.671
Oh, and winner gets this hat.

10:53.771 --> 10:55.935
Ooh!

10:56.935 --> 10:58.209
I think I would have preferred

10:58.309 --> 11:00.458
you and me getting drunk
somewhere.

11:00.558 --> 11:00.915
Oh, me too.

11:01.015 --> 11:03.665
But you know, they wanted to
do something special for you.

11:03.765 --> 11:07.869
Yep. Well, destroying them
on the track will be special.

11:07.969 --> 11:10.160
Yeah. (CACKLES)

11:10.260 --> 11:14.174
-Gabriel, where is my car?
-It's just over here.

11:17.173 --> 11:19.821
Stop freaking out! Jesus.

11:19.921 --> 11:23.569
Mum, while we look, how can we
make your Mother's Day better?

11:23.669 --> 11:26.501
Tell me why am I a good mother.

11:27.084 --> 11:27.567
Because...

11:27.667 --> 11:31.606
..you care for us and you make
a lot of money for us.

11:31.706 --> 11:34.272
Good. Now you.

11:34.372 --> 11:37.852
Gabriel, tell me right now
why am I a good mother?

11:37.952 --> 11:40.309
Because you appreciate my jokes.

11:40.409 --> 11:42.350
But that's not even about me,
Gabriel.

11:42.450 --> 11:46.265
Ready? Why do women wear
make-up and perfume?

11:46.365 --> 11:48.304
Because they're ugly
and they reek!

11:50.111 --> 11:50.970
Carajo!

11:51.070 --> 11:53.842
SONG: ♪ Pull up, pull up
in the German

11:53.942 --> 11:55.092
♪ Your crew look nervous

11:55.192 --> 11:56.384
♪ Your gang came from the circus

11:56.484 --> 11:57.966
♪ You will never, ever
make no earnings

11:58.066 --> 12:00.673
♪ Pull up, pull up
in the German... ♪

12:00.773 --> 12:02.213
(SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

12:02.313 --> 12:04.629
♪ You will never, ever
make no earnings

12:04.729 --> 12:06.750
♪ They ain't about
so don't bother... ♪

12:06.850 --> 12:09.100
(CLEARS THROAT LOUDLY)

12:09.768 --> 12:13.806
(REEMA LAUGHS) Yeah, well...
(CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY)

12:15.264 --> 12:17.054
Vince!

12:18.844 --> 12:19.911
-Reema!
-Hi!

12:20.011 --> 12:21.410
I didn't see you guys there.

12:21.510 --> 12:24.575
-(ISHANI LAUGHS)
-Oh, happy Mother's Day.

12:24.675 --> 12:25.253
Oh, thanks, Vince.

12:25.263 --> 12:27.490
Would you like to join us
for a quick champagne?

12:27.590 --> 12:31.379
-Why not!
-ISHANI: Great! (CHUCKLES)

12:32.545 --> 12:34.336
Wow, look at this.

12:35.419 --> 12:36.901
VINCE: Thank you. Thank you.

12:37.001 --> 12:39.732
Um, yeah, how's your day
been so far?

12:39.832 --> 12:40.358
So good.

12:40.458 --> 12:42.439
Yes, because I am
the perfect daughter.

12:42.539 --> 12:46.853
Breakfast in bed and then
champagne all afternoon.

12:46.953 --> 12:49.352
-(ISHANI CHUCKLES)
-Wow! So spoiled!

12:49.452 --> 12:50.018
ISHANI: So spoiled.

12:50.118 --> 12:53.183
She deserves celebration for
bringing me into this world,

12:53.283 --> 12:54.225
don't you, Mum?

12:54.325 --> 12:56.864
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

12:57.904 --> 13:00.679
So, what did you give your mum?

13:00.779 --> 13:01.719
Um...

13:01.819 --> 13:03.010
..I was just gonna go see her.

13:03.110 --> 13:05.967
Um, might grab her
some flowers on the way.

13:06.067 --> 13:07.734
ISHANI: Mmm.

13:09.149 --> 13:10.481
Yep.

13:15.228 --> 13:16.977
Are you OK?

13:18.268 --> 13:20.167
Yep. I don't know.

13:20.267 --> 13:23.598
I have to tell Mum about
Ariel being pregnant.

13:24.515 --> 13:25.039
She's pregnant?

13:25.139 --> 13:27.622
Three months.
Yeah, just found out.

13:27.722 --> 13:29.245
REEMA: Oh, my God!

13:29.345 --> 13:32.760
You're actually gonna
be a dad with her?

13:33.260 --> 13:35.158
And...and Talia.

13:35.258 --> 13:37.616
I just don't know
what Mum's gonna think.

13:37.716 --> 13:40.405
I just don't know how it's
gonna play out with her -

13:40.505 --> 13:42.820
whether she'll wanna
own it or...

13:42.920 --> 13:44.694
Yeah, no, I don't know.

13:44.794 --> 13:48.026
I mean, it's...it's
pretty shocking.

13:48.126 --> 13:50.689
Right? For your mum.

13:50.789 --> 13:55.122
Having this suddenly land on her
could be tough.

13:59.202 --> 14:02.350
Right. Right, well, I'm sorry
for bringing this up.

14:02.450 --> 14:04.099
It's just on my mind
and I wanted to...

14:04.199 --> 14:06.348
ISHANI: No, Vince, it's fine.
It's fine.

14:06.448 --> 14:07.223
Top-up?

14:07.323 --> 14:09.821
Sorry, no. No, thank you.

14:10.738 --> 14:11.970
I better...

14:12.070 --> 14:13.595
Happy Mother's Day.

14:13.695 --> 14:16.067
ISHANI: Thanks, Vince.

14:22.314 --> 14:25.646
(SUBTLE MUSIC)

14:26.936 --> 14:29.809
Hoo! Let's do it.

14:34.931 --> 14:36.081
(GRUNTS)

14:36.181 --> 14:38.580
It's like a bloody oubliette.

14:38.680 --> 14:40.078
(EDITH CHUCKLES)

14:40.178 --> 14:42.202
I'm not gonna let you win,
Angela.

14:42.302 --> 14:43.201
You won't have to.

14:43.301 --> 14:45.492
Seriously, guys, go easy.
I don't wanna crash.

14:45.592 --> 14:47.657
VOICE OVER LOUDSPEAKER:
<i>Drivers, get ready!</i>

14:47.757 --> 14:49.282
<i>Engage power core!</i>

14:49.382 --> 14:50.654
<i>Prepare for battle!</i>

14:50.754 --> 14:52.904
<i>Three, two, one.</i>

14:53.004 --> 14:54.778
<i>-Race!
</i>-(BUZZER SOUNDS)

14:54.878 --> 14:55.444
(WHOOPS)

14:55.544 --> 14:59.900
('HAVING A HARD TIME' BY
EDDY CURRENT SUPPRESSION RING)

15:00.000 --> 15:01.898
-Whoo!
-BOWIE: Get out of it!

15:01.998 --> 15:03.981
(BOWIE AND ANGIE
SHOUT AND WHOOP)

15:04.081 --> 15:05.729
(BOWIE CACKLES)

15:05.829 --> 15:07.644
ANGIE: Cheating!

15:07.744 --> 15:09.478
BOWIE: Bowie in front!

15:09.578 --> 15:10.893
(WHOOPS)

15:10.993 --> 15:12.101
Oh, come on!

15:12.201 --> 15:14.142
Out of the way, Edith!

15:14.242 --> 15:15.350
(EDITH SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY)

15:15.450 --> 15:18.240
(SOFT, ETHEREAL MUSIC)

15:22.071 --> 15:23.053
-(ROCK MUSIC RESUMES)
-BOWIE: Whoo-hoo!

15:23.153 --> 15:26.926
Bowie, you've gotta let
the car behind you pass!

15:27.026 --> 15:28.858
(GROWLS)

15:29.524 --> 15:31.090
(OTHERS SHOUT)

15:31.190 --> 15:34.629
(SOFT, ETHEREAL MUSIC)

15:34.729 --> 15:37.877
ANGIE: You're cheating, Bowie!
Come on!

15:37.977 --> 15:40.560
(LAUGHS MANIACALLY)

15:41.808 --> 15:43.749
(LAUGHS JOYOUSLY)

15:43.849 --> 15:46.223
BOWIE: Eat it, Angela!

15:47.473 --> 15:49.496
Ahhh! Urgh!

15:49.596 --> 15:51.761
ANGIE: Sucked in, Bowie!

15:52.220 --> 15:54.493
I'm coming to get ya, Boz!

15:54.593 --> 15:58.116
So long, sucker!

15:58.216 --> 16:01.631
Ha-ha! Whoo!

16:06.045 --> 16:08.376
(CACKLES)

16:12.291 --> 16:14.148
-AUTOMATED VOICE:<i>Winner!
</i> -Yeah!

16:14.248 --> 16:16.397
Suck it! Suck it, all of you!

16:16.497 --> 16:19.703
-BOWIE: No, no, no, no.
-ANGIE: Suck it!

16:20.911 --> 16:22.976
-Rematch.
-Bring it!

16:23.076 --> 16:25.225
-BOWIE: Yeah.
-No. No, no, no.

16:25.325 --> 16:27.597
-Bowie, this is perfect.
-(LAUGHS)

16:27.697 --> 16:28.360
Mate, it's Mother's Day.

16:28.370 --> 16:33.304
Edith, it is a bullshit made-up
day to sell flowers and cards.

16:33.404 --> 16:35.692
We have to beat her!

16:36.319 --> 16:37.967
(LAUGHS) Hey!

16:38.067 --> 16:39.633
That was fun!

16:39.733 --> 16:41.299
Mum, you beat us!

16:41.399 --> 16:43.340
Happy Mother's Day!

16:43.440 --> 16:44.058
Thank you, darling.

16:44.068 --> 16:46.796
It will be, yeah,
after I destroy Bowie again.

16:46.896 --> 16:48.462
Oh, yeah? Yeah, bring it on.

16:48.562 --> 16:52.766
DOM: Let's let them
race by themselves, huh?

17:15.254 --> 17:16.903
Are you OK, Dad?

17:17.003 --> 17:19.043
Yeah.

17:19.792 --> 17:21.208
I'm OK.

17:21.542 --> 17:24.914
I remember all the good things
about her.

17:26.165 --> 17:28.037
She was soft.

17:28.787 --> 17:30.995
Made me feel safe.

17:32.202 --> 17:33.684
She was smart.

17:33.784 --> 17:35.657
And cool.

17:37.116 --> 17:39.240
(BERNADITA SNIFFLES)

17:39.739 --> 17:42.904
REEMA: Come on, then.
What'd she say?

17:43.487 --> 17:45.219
I couldn't tell my mum.

17:45.319 --> 17:47.277
I tried.

17:47.485 --> 17:50.400
"I helped Ariel get pregnant."

17:50.608 --> 17:52.965
Mum's hated every single girl
that's come near me

17:53.065 --> 17:54.423
except for you, Ree.

17:54.523 --> 17:56.813
I haven't come near you.

17:57.563 --> 18:00.893
I looked at her...and froze up.

18:01.310 --> 18:02.043
Couldn't handle it.

18:02.143 --> 18:05.083
Well, you're gonna
have to handle it!

18:05.183 --> 18:05.665
ISHANI: Yeah.

18:05.765 --> 18:08.722
How have you not
thought this through?

18:14.553 --> 18:17.342
Another bottle here, please!

18:18.758 --> 18:20.241
EDITH: Have you called Mum yet?

18:20.341 --> 18:23.031
Not yet. Where is she?

18:23.131 --> 18:24.238
I don't know.

18:24.338 --> 18:25.280
Last I heard, she was...

18:25.380 --> 18:28.361
..walking the Nakasendo Trail
in Japan or something.

18:28.461 --> 18:31.524
Does it reflect poorly
on you and I that our mother

18:31.624 --> 18:36.440
spends her life as far away
from us as she possibly can?

18:36.540 --> 18:39.247
She's living for her now.

18:40.579 --> 18:43.517
-Should we call her?
-She won't answer!

18:43.617 --> 18:44.809
Come on.

18:44.909 --> 18:46.891
Never know.

18:46.991 --> 18:48.807
-(CLEARS THROAT)
-(PHONE RINGING TONE)

18:48.907 --> 18:51.431
RECORDED VOICE:The number you
have dialled is not available.

18:51.531 --> 18:53.179
Leave a message after the tone.

18:53.279 --> 18:54.720
-(BEEP!)
-Hi, Mum!

18:54.820 --> 18:55.886
It's Dom and Edie.

18:55.986 --> 18:59.301
Hey, Mum! We're...we're thinking
of you on Mother's Day.

18:59.401 --> 19:02.799
Hope you're having a good time,
wherever you are.

19:02.899 --> 19:06.131
Look forward to seeing you
sometime.

19:06.231 --> 19:07.838
Love you, Mum!

19:07.938 --> 19:09.853
Yeah.

19:11.684 --> 19:13.959
ANGIE: Who is the winner?

19:14.059 --> 19:15.250
Who is the winner?

19:15.350 --> 19:17.457
Yeah, nah, 'cause
you were cheating.

19:17.557 --> 19:20.163
Like, you have to let
the racer behind pass.

19:20.263 --> 19:21.621
And she didn't even...

19:21.721 --> 19:22.954
Best Mother's Day ever.

19:23.054 --> 19:24.619
Yeah, well, 'cause, like...

19:24.719 --> 19:26.119
Namaste, darling.

19:26.219 --> 19:26.993
Get stuffed! Mum!

19:27.093 --> 19:30.449
Happy Mother's Day,
you...competitive witch!

19:30.549 --> 19:33.738
Bowie, you're being
very un-Bowie.

19:33.838 --> 19:35.197
-Chill, man.
-Yeah.

19:35.297 --> 19:37.695
Just pretend you let me win
if you like.

19:37.795 --> 19:39.986
-(BOWIE CONTINUES RANTING)
-Oh, moan.

19:40.086 --> 19:41.360
Sore loser.

19:41.460 --> 19:43.167
Where's Oly?

19:44.791 --> 19:46.165
Oh, oh!

19:46.581 --> 19:49.039
Oh, God bless her.

19:53.619 --> 19:55.494
(BIRDS CHIRP)

19:57.616 --> 19:59.598
Bueno, ya, I'm calling
the police.

19:59.698 --> 20:00.069
Mum, no!

20:00.079 --> 20:01.931
What am I supposed to do,
Gabriel, huh?

20:02.031 --> 20:04.322
No, because you clearly lost it.

20:05.112 --> 20:07.428
Why do you have to be
such a bitch?

20:07.528 --> 20:08.985
Excuse me?

20:09.152 --> 20:11.508
All you do is lecture me
all the time.

20:11.608 --> 20:13.674
Because you do things
like steal my car.

20:13.774 --> 20:14.881
Of course I do!

20:14.981 --> 20:17.189
I fucking hate you.

20:19.229 --> 20:20.561
Don't.

20:21.145 --> 20:22.086
Don't say that.

20:22.186 --> 20:23.960
Everything I do, I mess up.

20:24.060 --> 20:26.475
(CHUCKLES) I can't help it.

20:27.682 --> 20:29.374
Yes, you can.

20:29.474 --> 20:32.388
Gabriel, you're my little boy.

20:34.220 --> 20:34.911
OK?

20:35.011 --> 20:37.135
(MUTTERS) OK.

20:40.216 --> 20:43.299
Hey, Mum, I found the car.

20:52.293 --> 20:54.108
SEBASTIAN: Nuh.

20:54.208 --> 20:55.358
SEBASTIAN: Uh-uh.

20:55.458 --> 20:57.415
(CAR BEEPS)

20:57.748 --> 20:59.997
Happy Mother's Day, Mum.

21:01.662 --> 21:02.228
Not yet.

21:02.328 --> 21:04.685
I wanna know that
I'm a good mother

21:04.785 --> 21:05.851
that raised good children.

21:05.951 --> 21:07.475
So give your brother a hug.

21:07.575 --> 21:09.491
(SIGHS) What? No!

21:12.947 --> 21:15.429
Now tell each other
that you love each other.

21:15.529 --> 21:16.179
-Oh, my God.
-Why?

21:16.279 --> 21:19.177
Why? Because I'm not gonna
be here forever, Gabriel.

21:19.277 --> 21:22.051
And you'll only have
each other to rely on,

21:22.151 --> 21:23.466
so I wanna hear the love.

21:23.566 --> 21:25.522
Love you, Gab.

21:26.023 --> 21:26.923
Love you, Seb.

21:27.023 --> 21:29.729
There. I'm happy.

21:35.309 --> 21:36.641
Mum?

21:37.683 --> 21:41.331
Mum, this isn't funny.
We helped you find the car.

21:41.431 --> 21:43.871
Yeah, mi amor. Thank you.
Now, you know what?

21:43.971 --> 21:46.702
You can think about your
punishment while you walk home.

21:46.802 --> 21:48.368
I didn't do anything wrong!

21:48.468 --> 21:50.575
Ay, I know, mi vida.
You're my good boy.

21:50.675 --> 21:53.157
So maybe you can teach him
something, sí?

21:53.257 --> 21:55.488
And see you boys at the house

21:55.588 --> 21:58.130
in an hour...ish.

21:59.045 --> 21:59.612
Maybe.

21:59.712 --> 22:02.335
(STARTS ENGINE) 'Bye.

22:29.568 --> 22:33.775
Sorry! Sorry, sorry, sorry,
sorry, sorry, sorry.

22:41.020 --> 22:42.602
N-n-no!

22:49.890 --> 22:52.123
Sorry this day is sad.

22:52.223 --> 22:53.330
Thank you.

22:53.430 --> 22:55.453
But it's not, Sorpresa.

22:55.553 --> 22:59.302
Why don't we have some fun?

23:06.922 --> 23:07.946
You wanna have a party?

23:08.046 --> 23:09.113
JACINDA: Yay, a party!

23:09.213 --> 23:11.610
-SANTI: We can dance with Ita?
-OLY: Hello?

23:11.710 --> 23:14.567
Mum, where's your hat?

23:14.667 --> 23:17.691
Oh, Grangie won it.

23:17.791 --> 23:19.814
Are you ready?
She's just waiting outside.

23:19.914 --> 23:22.396
Oly, is your mother here too?

23:22.496 --> 23:24.187
Bring her in!

23:24.287 --> 23:26.435
And Dum-Dum and Aunty Edie.

23:26.535 --> 23:29.076
Bring them all in!

23:30.367 --> 23:32.307
(EDITH WHISPERS) I don't know
what I'm doing here.

23:32.407 --> 23:35.638
(MUTTERS) If I have to be here,
so do you.

23:35.738 --> 23:38.071
DOM: Yeah, two fists.

23:38.986 --> 23:40.177
Oh, Alejandro.

23:40.277 --> 23:41.677
Thank you so much
for inviting us.

23:41.777 --> 23:44.591
-This is really nice.
-Our pleasure, amigo.

23:44.691 --> 23:46.339
-Our pleasure.
-Oh, that's a great idea.

23:46.439 --> 23:48.131
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

23:48.231 --> 23:50.462
Cheers. Thank you.

23:50.562 --> 23:52.335
Hello, hello!

23:52.435 --> 23:53.710
What's going on here?

23:53.810 --> 23:55.709
Oh, Dita wanted to celebrate.

23:55.809 --> 23:59.431
Ahh. Are my sons here yet?

24:01.140 --> 24:02.455
Hi.

24:02.555 --> 24:05.662
Dita invited us in.
Hope you don't mind.

24:05.762 --> 24:07.661
You're looking better.

24:07.761 --> 24:09.743
Ohh! Yeah, mmm. Thanks.

24:09.843 --> 24:12.009
ROSA: Interesting hairdo.

24:12.424 --> 24:13.616
Yeah, cancer chic.

24:13.716 --> 24:19.005
Uh, Rosa, care for
some French champagne?

24:19.419 --> 24:21.961
-Sí.
-(DOM CHORTLES) Sí!

24:22.378 --> 24:24.484
-Cin cin.
-Happy Mother's Day.

24:24.584 --> 24:25.609
Thank you!

24:25.709 --> 24:29.191
(SALSA MUSIC PLAYS)

24:29.291 --> 24:30.564
ANGIE: He stole your car?

24:30.664 --> 24:33.188
It's...it's a Mercedes,
isn't it?

24:33.288 --> 24:35.310
He's lucky he's alive, huh?

24:35.410 --> 24:37.393
Oh, yeah, but then
when you found it,

24:37.493 --> 24:39.850
that's better than flowers.

24:39.950 --> 24:41.974
(LAUGHS)

24:42.074 --> 24:45.806
I want to dance. You like
Latin dancing, don't you?

24:45.906 --> 24:48.195
Yeah, I used to.

24:49.403 --> 24:50.928
Ay, fuck it!

24:51.028 --> 24:51.802
Come on.

24:51.902 --> 24:55.566
(SALSA MUSIC CONTINUES)

25:06.934 --> 25:08.583
To all the mothers!

25:08.683 --> 25:10.515
Your day.

25:12.431 --> 25:13.872
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

25:13.972 --> 25:16.888
-(ALL CHEER)
-Happy Mother's Day!

25:17.636 --> 25:20.326
-ANGIE: Whoo-hoo!
-DITA: Happy Mother's Day.

25:20.426 --> 25:21.826
Hey, fellas.

25:21.926 --> 25:24.491
Mother's Day present? Nice.

25:24.591 --> 25:26.798
SEBASTIAN: It's a birdbath,
Mama.

25:27.007 --> 25:31.320
I bought it. Dad paid for it.
It was second-hand.

25:31.420 --> 25:33.486
-Really?
-Yeah. It was!

25:33.586 --> 25:36.584
Ay, put it down there.
Put it down there.

25:37.583 --> 25:39.540
(GABRIEL LAUGHS)

25:48.119 --> 25:50.933
Why are you not dancing,
Aunty Edie?

25:51.033 --> 25:53.348
Oh, you... I'm not a mum.

25:53.448 --> 25:54.723
Oh, sorry about that.

25:54.823 --> 25:59.345
Oh, no, that's OK.
I am totally OK being just me.

25:59.445 --> 26:01.136
And being part of your life.

26:01.236 --> 26:02.594
You don't need to be a mum.

26:02.694 --> 26:04.508
You're an excellent Aunty Edith.

26:04.608 --> 26:07.732
Aww! Thanks, cool girl.

26:08.815 --> 26:10.756
Fuck it. Come on, let's dance.

26:10.856 --> 26:13.295
Yes! Oh, and swear jar.

26:13.395 --> 26:15.794
(SIGHS) Got me again.

26:15.894 --> 26:17.685
I'll pay ya later.

26:25.888 --> 26:27.637
Santiago?

26:34.175 --> 26:35.532
-Right now?
-Oly.

26:35.632 --> 26:39.237
-SANTI: No, no, no. It's OK.
-Go with him, please.

26:39.337 --> 26:39.822
Help carry.

26:39.922 --> 26:43.486
It's OK. I don't need you
to come with me.

26:43.586 --> 26:47.125
Go. Both. Now.

26:47.959 --> 26:49.749
Milk and bread.

26:50.790 --> 26:54.604
Don't forget your hat, Mum.
It's sunny out there.

26:54.704 --> 26:57.186
Oh. Thank you!

26:57.286 --> 27:00.160
('PASADO Y OLVIDO'
BY PEHUENCHE PLAYS)

27:05.740 --> 27:10.238
(SONG IN SPANISH PLAYS)

27:27.652 --> 27:29.010
The hat really suits you.

27:29.110 --> 27:31.526
-Really?
-(LAUGHS) Yeah.

27:32.066 --> 27:34.357
I really liked the card.

27:35.687 --> 27:38.021
I was worried it'd upset you.

27:39.937 --> 27:41.751
I really like that you're
doing your art again.

27:41.850 --> 27:46.100
It's really special. I think
you should keep doing it.

27:48.596 --> 27:50.347
Thanks, Oly.

27:56.591 --> 27:59.741
It was what you wrote in
the card that made me feel...

27:59.841 --> 28:02.173
..weird this morning.

28:04.671 --> 28:06.504
I sort of...

28:07.419 --> 28:08.860
..lost it this year.

28:08.960 --> 28:09.777
And it's 'cause when you said

28:09.877 --> 28:12.957
that you wanted to introduce
J to Keeks.

28:13.417 --> 28:13.983
That was your idea.

28:14.082 --> 28:17.480
No, it wasn't. You said
that you were gonna go camping.

28:17.580 --> 28:18.605
No, I wasn't... That was only...

28:18.705 --> 28:21.370
Can you just...
Can you let me finish?

28:21.703 --> 28:26.975
SONG: ♪ There are no words
I have to say... ♪

28:27.076 --> 28:28.225
(OLY SIGHS)

28:28.325 --> 28:31.098
♪ In this moment... ♪

28:31.197 --> 28:35.678
I really thought that us
breaking up was a good idea,

28:35.779 --> 28:37.778
that it was...

28:38.319 --> 28:39.676
..you know, a sensible decision.

28:39.776 --> 28:42.133
♪ You're asking me
if I'm OK... ♪

28:42.233 --> 28:45.130
And then when you told me
that you wanted them to meet,

28:45.231 --> 28:48.312
I guess the whole thing just...

28:49.811 --> 28:52.019
..became really real.

28:53.850 --> 28:57.124
(THINKS)I realised
that maybe I made a mistake.

28:57.224 --> 29:01.181
♪ Make me lose my focus... ♪

29:01.928 --> 29:02.704
(GIRL LAUGHS)

29:02.803 --> 29:05.370
♪ And all these parts of me... ♪

29:05.470 --> 29:09.575
Hey, I really wanna listen
to this, but, um, it's Keeks.

29:09.675 --> 29:11.740
-Hey!
-KEEKS: Hey!

29:11.840 --> 29:13.198
(LAUGHS)

29:13.299 --> 29:13.947
Hi! Are you Oly?

29:14.048 --> 29:16.655
I mean...I know you are.
I've seen your picture.

29:16.754 --> 29:19.444
(LAUGHS) Sorry. I'm Keeks.

29:19.543 --> 29:20.568
Hey.

29:20.668 --> 29:23.418
Did he make a fuss of you?

29:24.417 --> 29:24.942
Sorry?

29:25.042 --> 29:27.856
I told him
to make a fuss of you.

29:27.956 --> 29:28.357
Ohh!

29:28.456 --> 29:30.912
-Oh! (LAUGHS)
-(CHUCKLES)

29:31.495 --> 29:32.187
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

29:32.287 --> 29:35.517
♪ All these things
that make me... ♪

29:35.617 --> 29:36.935
KEEKS: Cool shoes.

29:37.034 --> 29:39.698
♪ Lose my focus... ♪

29:41.407 --> 29:43.181
Um, I should get going,
'cause...

29:43.281 --> 29:46.303
..um, I'll get the milk
for Bernadita,

29:46.404 --> 29:48.345
'cause she needs it for the...

29:48.445 --> 29:49.551
SANTI: OK.

29:49.651 --> 29:55.382
♪ Before you came... ♪

29:55.482 --> 29:56.839
SANTI: Hey!

29:56.938 --> 29:58.713
KEEKS: Hey! (LAUGHS)

29:58.812 --> 30:00.754
♪ Before you

30:00.854 --> 30:06.515
♪ Came

30:08.932 --> 30:14.886
♪ I know you think
I'm being cold

30:15.345 --> 30:22.425
♪ But I can't bear
to look at you today

30:26.089 --> 30:30.028
♪ 'Cause every single time I do

30:30.128 --> 30:34.625
♪ I fear it might be
the last time

30:35.957 --> 30:37.565
♪ That you'll

30:37.665 --> 30:43.021
♪ See me this way

30:43.120 --> 30:48.741
♪ Way

30:53.697 --> 30:57.361
♪ Way

31:00.527 --> 31:02.925
♪ So draw your lines

31:03.024 --> 31:06.773
♪ Upon my skin

31:07.438 --> 31:14.143
♪ For the very final time... ♪
